        "content": "<p>I have the following assumptions in Lean:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">hyp_frac_divergence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Tendsto</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span>\n<span class=\"n\">hyp_y_attop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Tendsto</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span>\n<span class=\"n\">hyp_y_strictlymono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">StrictMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I want to prove:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Tendsto</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Intuitively, this follows because the discrete derivative of <code>x</code> over <code>y</code> tends to infinity, and <code>y</code> tends to infinity as well.</p>\n<p>Are there any existing lemmas or standard techniques in Lean's mathlib to help prove this directly?<br>\n Perhaps something like a monotone comparison principle or a sum lower-bound argument?</p>\n<p>why I need to prove it because, I wanna prove stolz theorem when th<br>\ne limit is infinite</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">StolzPosInfinity</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hyp_y_strictlymono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">StrictMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hyp_y_attop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Tendsto</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hyp_frac_divergence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">Tendsto</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> 